OL,3,CWelsh NHS could refuse to offer
OL,4,Cassisted dying services, says minister
OL,6,FPlans to change the law to legalise
OL,7,Fassisted dying in Wales and England
OL,8,Fwere agreed in the House of Commons in
OL,9,FJune which voted to pass the
OL,10,FTerminally Ill Adults (End of Life)
OL,11,FBill by 314 to 291. Of Wales' 32 MPs,
OL,12,F24 backed the bill, seven voted
OL,13,Fagainst and one did not vote.
OL,15,FThe proposed law-change will next be
OL,16,Fdebated in the House of Lords.
