OL,3,CWelsh NHS could refuse to offer
OL,4,Cassisted dying services, says minister
OL,6,FHealth is devolved, so the
OL,7,Fimplementation of any assisted dying
OL,8,Fservice would be carried out through
OL,9,Fthe Welsh NHS which is controlled by
OL,10,Fthe Welsh Government and ultimately
OL,11,Fanswerable to the Senedd itself.
OL,13,FIn a vote last October on the
OL,14,Fprinciple of assisted dying, Senedd
OL,15,Fmembers including the First Minister
OL,16,Fand Health Secretary voted against it,
OL,17,Fwhich means there is every chance that
OL,18,FMSs could vote to block it.
