OL,3,CWelsh NHS could refuse to offer
OL,4,Cassisted dying services, says minister
OL,6,FThe cabinet secretary said: "In order
OL,7,Ffor those regulations to be laid,
OL,8,Fwhich would be necessary in order for,
OL,9,Ffor example, the NHS to provide this
OL,10,Fservice in Wales, then a Welsh
OL,11,FGovernment...would need to make a
OL,12,Fpolicy decision to be open to
OL,13,Fintroducing the service, then to lay
OL,14,Fthe regulations and for the Senedd to
OL,15,Fapprove those.
OL,17,F"So that's in relation to services
OL,18,Fprovided in the public sector...by the
OL,19,FNHS, because that's within devolved
OL,20,Fcompetence."
